  "style": "APA",
  "texts": [
    "Another sophisticated method for batch correction is the Mutual Nearest Neighbors (MNN) technique (128), which uses shared nearest neighbor information to correct batch discrepancies.",
    "By aligning nearest neighbors across batches, MNN effectively harmonizes datasets.",
    "In terms of data correlation network, MMvec, inspired by word2vec, uses matrix factorization to analyze the co-occurrence patterns of microbes and metabolites, offering insights such as the metabolites produced by microbes in specific diseases (135).",
    "Similarly, Similarity Network Fusion (SNF) integrates multiple omics datasets by creating separate networks for each data type and merging them using non-linear fusion techniques based on message-passing theory (158).",
    "This integration deepens as the networks converge through successive iterations."
  ],
